#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:2
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Descripción General"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:4
msgid ""
"The :mod:`~qilisdk.cost_functions` module turns the raw outputs returned "
"by functionals into single scalar values that optimizers can minimize. "
"Each cost function inspects the "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` produced"
" by a backend and evaluates a problem-specific metric such as an "
"observable expectation value or the energy of an abstract optimization "
"model."
msgstr ""
"El módulo :mod:`~qilisdk.cost_functions` convierte las salidas brutas "
"devueltas por los funcionales en valores escalares únicos que los "
"optimizadores pueden minimizar. Cada función de coste inspecciona el "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` producido "
"por un backend y evalúa una métrica específica del problema, como el valor "
"esperado de un observable o la energía de un modelo de optimización abstracto."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:9
msgid "Cost functions are used to:"
msgstr "Las funciones de coste se utilizan para:"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:11
msgid ""
"score intermediate iterations inside a "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.variational_program.VariationalProgram`"
msgstr ""
"puntuar iteraciones intermedias dentro de un "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.variational_program.VariationalProgram`"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:12
msgid ""
"post-process "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` samples "
"into meaningful costs"
msgstr ""
"post-procesar muestras de "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` en "
"costes significativos"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:13
msgid ""
"translate "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` states "
"into expectation values"
msgstr ""
"traducir estados de "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` en "
"valores esperados"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:17
msgid "CostFunction Interface"
msgstr "Interfaz CostFunction"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:19
msgid ""
"The abstract :class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` "
"base class exposes a single public method, "
":meth:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction.compute_cost`. "
"It dispatches on the concrete type of the functional result and calls the"
" appropriate protected hook:"
msgstr ""
"La clase base abstracta "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` expone un "
"único método público, "
":meth:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction.compute_cost`. "
"Este despacha según el tipo concreto del resultado funcional y llama al "
"gancho protegido apropiado:"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:23
msgid ""
"It dispatches on the content of the "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult`, "
"inspecting the available readout results (samples, expectation values, "
"final state) to compute the cost."
msgstr ""
"Despacha según el contenido del "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult`, "
"inspeccionando los resultados de lectura disponibles (muestras, valores "
"esperados, estado final) para calcular el coste."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:26
msgid ""
"If your workflow introduces new functional result types you can subclass "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` and register "
"additional handlers in ``self._handlers`` or override the protected "
"methods above. Custom implementations must return a real or complex "
"number that represents the score you want to optimize."
msgstr ""
"Si su flujo de trabajo introduce nuevos tipos de resultados funcionales, "
"puede crear subclases de "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` y registrar "
"manejadores adicionales en ``self._handlers`` o sobreescribir los métodos "
"protegidos anteriores. Las implementaciones personalizadas deben devolver "
"un número real o complejo que represente la puntuación que desea optimizar."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:32
msgid "Cost Functions in Variational Programs"
msgstr "Funciones de coste en programas variacionales"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:34
msgid ""
"Variational workflows combine a parameterized "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional.Functional`, a classical "
"optimizer, and a "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction`. At each "
"optimizer iteration the backend executes the functional, obtains a "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` object, "
"and feeds it into the configured cost function to obtain the scalar that "
"drives the optimization loop."
msgstr ""
"Los flujos de trabajo variacionales combinan un "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional.Functional` parametrizado, un "
"optimizador clásico y una "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction`. En cada "
"iteración del optimizador, el backend ejecuta el funcional, obtiene un "
"objeto :class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` y "
"lo introduce en la función de coste configurada para obtener el escalar que "
"impulsa el bucle de optimización."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions_overview.rst:69
msgid ""
"Swapping the cost function lets you explore alternative objective "
"definitions without touching the functional itself. For example, you can "
"start with "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.observable_cost_function.ObservableCostFunction`"
" to reproduce a physics-inspired energy expectation and later try "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.model_cost_function.ModelCostFunction` to"
" include constraint penalties from a combinatorial problem."
msgstr ""
"Cambiar la función de coste le permite explorar definiciones alternativas "
"del objetivo sin modificar el funcional en sí. Por ejemplo, puede comenzar "
"con "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.observable_cost_function.ObservableCostFunction`"
" para reproducir una expectativa de energía inspirada en la física y luego "
"probar "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.model_cost_function.ModelCostFunction` para "
"incluir penalizaciones por restricciones de un problema combinatorio."
